# GLOBAL git ignore (core.excludesFile / XDG ~/.config/git/ignore) — applies to
# EVERY repo. So it holds ONLY universals: OS cruft, editor swap/undo files,
# secrets, and VCS merge debris. Language/build/tool artifacts (Python, Rust,
# LaTeX, Terraform, …) deliberately do NOT live here — an unanchored `lib/`,
# `var/`, `*.log`, etc. in a global file silently hides real source in unrelated
# repos. Put those in each project's own .gitignore (e.g. from gitignore.io).
# Was previously a 22-template gitignore.io dump; slimmed deliberately.

